The paper deals with the capacity of multi-user interference networks, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves cognitive networks, which is a subfield of networking (cs.NI). The use of side-information is another important aspect of the paper, which falls under the category of signal processing and information theory (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the use of Gaussian codebooks, which is a common technique in machine learning and pattern recognition (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses linear partial-cancellation schemes, which are relevant to communication engineering (cs.CE).
